Introduction

FANTASY BOYS is an 10-member multinational boy group under PocketDol Studio. The group was formed through the survival show 'Fantasy Boys'. They made their official debut on September 21, 2023, with their 1st mini album, "NEW TOMORROW."

They made their Japanese debut on June 19th, 2024, with the mini album, "Make a Fantasy".

The group initially had twelve members, including first-placer Yu Junwon. However, on August 23, 2023, PocketDol Studio announced that Junwon has departed from the group and FANTASY BOYS would debut as a 11 member group.

Ksoul had been on an on-and-off hiatus since September of 2023 due to the deteriorating health of his father and grandmother. It was announced in early March that his father has passed away on February 25th. On January 24, 2025, KSoul discovered online that PocketDol Studio had announced his exit from FANTASY BOYS on their fan cafe. He will end all ties with both the group and the agency.
